#. <html><head><meta charset="UTF-8"><meta content="Pali text from the Mahāsaṅgīti Tipiṭaka Buddhavasse 2500" name="description"><title></title></head><body><div id="text" lang="pli"><section class="sutta" id="pi-tv-bu-vb-pc40"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc40:1.1"
msgid "Theravāda Vinaya"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc40:2.1"
msgid "Mahāvibhaṅga"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc40:3.1"
msgid "Pācittiyakaṇḍa"
msgstr "The chapter on confession (<i lang=\"pli\">pācittiya</i>)"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc40:4.1"
msgid "Bhojanavagga"
msgstr ""

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc40:5.1"
msgid "40. Dantaponasikkhāpada"
msgstr "Monks’ Confession 40: the training rule on tooth-cleaners"

#. </h1></div><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc40:6.1"
msgid ""
msgstr "Origin story"

#. </h2><h3>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc40:6.2"
msgid ""
msgstr "First sub-story"

#. </h3><p><a class="sc" id="1"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-pc.40.1"></a><a class="pts-vp-en" id="BD.2.344"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa848"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc40:6.3"
msgid "Tena samayena buddho bhagavā vesāliyaṃ viharati mahāvane kūṭāgārasālāyaṃ."
msgstr "At one time the Buddha was staying at Vesālī in the hall with the peaked roof in the Great Wood."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc40:6.4"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena aññataro bhikkhu sabbapaṃsukūliko susāne viharati."
msgstr "At that time a monk who only used discarded things was staying in a charnel ground."

#. VAR: paribhuñjati → bhuñjati (s1-3, pts1)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc40:6.5"
msgid "So manussehi diyyamānaṃ na icchati paṭiggahetuṃ, susānepi rukkhamūlepi ummārepi ayyavosāṭitakāni sāmaṃ gahetvā paribhuñjati."
msgstr "He disliked receiving what was given by people. Instead he would take whatever was offered to the dead at charnel grounds, at the foot of trees, or at thresholds, and he would use that."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc40:6.6"
msgid "Manussā ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—"
msgstr "People complained and criticized him,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc40:6.7"
msgid "“kathañhi nāma ayaṃ bhikkhu amhākaṃ ayyavosāṭitakāni sāmaṃ gahetvā paribhuñjissati."
msgstr "“How can this monk take the offerings to our ancestors and use them?"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc40:6.8"
msgid "Theroyaṃ bhikkhu vaṭharo manussamaṃsaṃ maññe khādatī”ti. One might even suspect him of eating human flesh!”"
msgstr "This monk is big and strong."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="2"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa849"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc40:7.1"
msgid "Assosuṃ kho bhikkhū tesaṃ manussānaṃ ujjhāyantānaṃ khiyyantānaṃ vipācentānaṃ."
msgstr "The monks heard the complaints of those people,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc40:7.2"
msgid "Ye te bhikkhū appicchā … pe …"
msgstr "and the monks of few desires …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc40:7.3"
msgid "te ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—"
msgstr "complained and criticized him,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc40:7.4"
msgid "“kathañhi nāma bhikkhu adinnaṃ mukhadvāraṃ āhāraṃ āharissatī”ti … pe …"
msgstr "“How can this monk eat food that has not been given?” …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc40:7.5"
msgid "“saccaṃ kira tvaṃ, bhikkhu, adinnaṃ mukhadvāraṃ āhāraṃ āharasī”ti?"
msgstr "“Is it true, monk, that you do this?”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc40:7.6"
msgid "“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti."
msgstr "“It’s true, Master.”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc40:7.7"
msgid "Vigarahi buddho bhagavā … pe …"
msgstr "The Buddha rebuked him, “…"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc40:7.8"
msgid "kathañhi nāma tvaṃ, moghapurisa, adinnaṃ mukhadvāraṃ āhāraṃ āharissasi."
msgstr "Foolish man, how can you eat food that has not been given?"

#. <a class="pts-vp-en" id="BD.2.345"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc40:7.9"
msgid "Netaṃ, moghapurisa, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya … pe …"
msgstr "This will not give rise to confidence in those without it …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc40:7.10"
msgid "evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—"
msgstr "And, monks, this training rule should be recited thus:"

#. </p><h3>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc40:8.1"
msgid ""
msgstr "Preliminary ruling"

#. </h3><p><a class="sc" id="3"></a><a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli4.90"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa850"></a>
#. <strong class="rule"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc40:8.2"
msgid "“Yo pana bhikkhu adinnaṃ mukhadvāraṃ āhāraṃ āhareyya, pācittiyan”ti."
msgstr "‘If a monk eats food that has not been given, he commits an offense entailing confession.’”"

#. </strong>
#. </p><p class="endsection"><a class="sc" id="4"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa851"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc40:9.1"
msgid "Evañcidaṃ bhagavatā bhikkhūnaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ paññattaṃ hoti."
msgstr "In this way the Master laid down this training rule for the monks."

#. </p><h3>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc40:10.1"
msgid ""
msgstr "Second sub-story"

#. </h3><p><a class="sc" id="5"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-pc.40.2"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa852"></a>
#. VAR: udakadantapone → udakadantapoṇe (s1-3, pts1, mr)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc40:10.2"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena bhikkhū udakadantapone kukkuccāyanti."
msgstr "Soon afterwards the monks did not use water or tooth-cleaners because they were afraid of wrongdoing."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc40:10.3"
msgid "Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ … pe …"
msgstr "They told the Master …"

#. <strong class="rule"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc40:10.4"
msgid "“anujānāmi, bhikkhave, udakadantaponaṃ sāmaṃ gahetvā paribhuñjituṃ."
msgstr "“Monks, I allow you to use water and tooth-cleaners after taking them yourselves."

#. </strong> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc40:10.5"
msgid "Evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—"
msgstr "And so, monks, this training rule should be recited thus:"

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc40:11.1"
msgid ""
msgstr "Final ruling"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="6"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa853"></a>
#. VAR: udakadantaponā → ... poṇā (s1-3, pts1)
#. <strong class="rule"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc40:11.2"
msgid "“Yo pana bhikkhu adinnaṃ mukhadvāraṃ āhāraṃ āhareyya, aññatra udakadantaponā, pācittiyan”ti."
msgstr "‘If a monk eats food that has not been given, except for water and tooth-cleaners, he commits an offense entailing confession.’”"

#. </strong> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc40:11.3"
msgid "(<em>40</em>:<strong>89</strong>)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc40:12.1"
msgid ""
msgstr "Definitions"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="7"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-pc.40.3"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-pc.40.3.1"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa854"></a>
#. <strong class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc40:12.2"
msgid "Yo panāti"
msgstr "A:"

#. </strong><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc40:12.3"
msgid "yo yādiso … pe …"
msgstr "whoever …"

#. </span>
#. <strong class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc40:12.4"
msgid "bhikkhūti"
msgstr "Monk:"

#. </strong><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc40:12.5"
msgid "… pe …"
msgstr "… he monk who has been given the full ordination by a complete Order through a procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements that is unchallengeable and fit to stand—"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc40:12.6"
msgid "ayaṃ imasmiṃ atthe adhippeto bhikkhūti."
msgstr "this sort of monk is meant in this case."

#. </span>
#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="8"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa855"></a>
#. <strong class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc40:13.1"
msgid "Adinnaṃ nāma"
msgstr "That has not been given:"

#. </strong><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc40:13.2"
msgid "appaṭiggahitakaṃ vuccati."
msgstr "what has not been received is what is meant."

#. </span>
#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="9"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa856"></a>
#. <strong class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc40:14.1"
msgid "Dinnaṃ nāma"
msgstr "Given:"

#. </strong><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc40:14.2"
msgid "kāyena vā kāyapaṭibaddhena vā nissaggiyena vā dente hatthapāse ṭhito kāyena vā kāyapaṭibaddhena vā paṭiggaṇhāti, etaṃ dinnaṃ nāma."
msgstr "standing within arm’s reach of one giving by body or by what is connected to his body or by releasing, he receives it by body or by what is connected to his body—this is called “given.”"

#. </span>
#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="10"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa857"></a>
#. <strong class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc40:15.1"
msgid "Āhāro nāma"
msgstr "Food:"

#. </strong><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc40:15.2"
msgid "udakadantaponaṃ ṭhapetvā yaṃ kiñci ajjhoharaṇīyaṃ, eso āhāro nāma."
msgstr "whatever is edible, apart from water and tooth-cleaners—this is called “food.”"

#. </span>
#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="11"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa858"></a>
#. <strong class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc40:16.1"
msgid "Aññatra udakadantaponāti"
msgstr "Except for water and tooth-cleaners:"

#. </strong><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc40:16.2"
msgid "ṭhapetvā udakadantaponaṃ."
msgstr "apart from water and tooth-cleaners."

#. </span>
#. </p><hr><p><a class="sc" id="12"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa859"></a><a class="pts-vp-en" id="BD.2.346"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc40:17.1"
msgid "“Khādissāmi bhuñjissāmī”ti gaṇhāti, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "If he takes it with the intention of eating it, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc40:17.2"
msgid "Ajjhohāre ajjhohāre āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr "For every mouthful, he commits an offense entailing confession."

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc40:18.1"
msgid ""
msgstr "Permutations"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="13"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-pc.40.3.2"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa860"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc40:18.2"
msgid "Appaṭiggahitake appaṭiggahitakasaññī adinnaṃ mukhadvāraṃ āhāraṃ āhāreti, aññatra udakadantaponā, āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr "If it has not been received, and he does not perceive it as received, and he eats it, except for water and tooth-cleaners, he commits an offense entailing confession."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc40:18.3"
msgid "Appaṭiggahitake vematiko adinnaṃ mukhadvāraṃ āhāraṃ āhāreti, aññatra udakadantaponā, āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr "If it has not been received, but he is unsure of it, and he eats it, except for water and tooth-cleaners, he commits an offense entailing confession."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc40:18.4"
msgid "Appaṭiggahitake paṭiggahitakasaññī adinnaṃ mukhadvāraṃ āhāraṃ āhāreti, aññatra udakadantaponā, āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr "If it has not been not received, but he perceives it as received, and he eats it, except for water and tooth-cleaners, he commits an offense entailing confession."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="14"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa861"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc40:19.1"
msgid "Paṭiggahitake appaṭiggahitakasaññī, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "If it has been received, but he does not perceive it as received, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc40:19.2"
msgid "Paṭiggahitake vematiko, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "If it has been received, but he is unsure if it has, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc40:19.3"
msgid "Paṭiggahitake paṭiggahitakasaññī, anāpatti."
msgstr "If it has been received, and he perceives it as received, there is no offense."

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc40:20.1"
msgid ""
msgstr "Non-offenses"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="15"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-pc.40.3.3"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa862"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc40:20.2"
msgid "Anāpatti—"
msgstr "There is no offense:"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc40:20.3"
msgid "udakadantapone,"
msgstr "if it is water or tooth-cleaners;"

#. <span class="note" hidden>These are dung, urine, ash, and clay, see <span class="ref">Mv.206.8</span>.</span> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc40:20.4"
msgid "cattāri mahāvikaṭāni sati paccaye asati kappiyakārake sāmaṃ gahetvā paribhuñjati,"
msgstr "if, when there is a reason, but there is no attendant, he himself takes the four filthy edibles and eats them;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc40:20.5"
msgid "ummattakassa,"
msgstr "if he is insane;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc40:20.6"
msgid "ādikammikassāti."
msgstr "if he is the first offender."

#. </p><hr><p class="endsutta"><a class="sc" id="16"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa863"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc40:21.1"
msgid "Dantaponasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ dasamaṃ."
msgstr "The tenth rule, the training rule on tooth-cleaners, is finished."

#. </p><p class="endchapter"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc40:21.2"
msgid "Bhojanavaggo catuttho."
msgstr "The fourth chapter on food is finished."

#. </p><p class="endsection summary"><a class="sc" id="17"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa864"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc40:22.1"
msgid "Tassuddānaṃ"
msgstr "This is the summary:"

#. </p><div class="uddana"><p><a class="sc" id="18"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa865"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc40:23.1"
msgid "Piṇḍo gaṇaṃ paraṃ pūvaṃ,"
msgstr "Alms, group, another, biscuit,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc40:23.2"
msgid "dve ca vuttā pavāraṇā;"
msgstr "And two on expressed satisfaction;"

#. <br>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc40:23.3"
msgid "Vikāle sannidhī khīraṃ,"
msgstr "At the wrong time, store, milk,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc40:23.4"
msgid "dantaponena te dasāti."
msgstr "And with tooth-cleaner: those are the ten."

